tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within normal limits except for a mildly elevated creatinine, which may indicate early renal impairment or dehydration. Glucose control (HbA1c and fasting glucose) is adequate. Electrolytes and urea are normal. Recommend clinical correlation for renal function and consideration of repeat testing or further evaluation if clinically indicated.
